commit.title: Print canonical projections as soon as they are registered
commit.message:
Print canonical projections as soon as they are registered

To see how canonical projections work and which head symbols they involve, we
needed to use `Print Canonical Projections` even if it is just after declaring a
new projection. When we do advanced canonical structure programming, we needed
to find a projection from hundreds of canonical projections printed.
Therefore, printing new canonical projections immediately by `Canonical` command
would help us a lot to understand how they work and to find wrong canonical
projections as soon as they are declared.
